artifacts.summary: Phase B blocker analysis: discovered that TruthLemma only needs reflexive forward_F (s >= t), eliminating the strict-future-witness problem. Also confirmed AddCommGroup constraint is vestigial.

partial_progress.details: Research complete with breakthrough finding: forward_F/backward_P can use reflexive witnesses (s >= t instead of s > t) because the TruthLemma contraposition argument works for both s = t and s > t. This eliminates the strict-future-witness problem that blocked 12+ prior approaches. Recommended path: weaken forward_F + drop vestigial AddCommGroup + build BFMCS on canonical frame directly.
